# Useful commands for use with composer:

configure composer components:
`composer install`

update composer components (if composer.json changed):
`composer update`

start internal webserver:
`php bin/console server:run 0.0.0.0:8000`

show routes:
`php bin/console debug:router`

create database schema diff:
`php bin/console doctrine:migrations:diff`

migrate to updated database schema (requires previous diff / manual migration script in src/MailWatch/Migrations/):
`php bin/console doctrine:migrations:migrate [version]`


#To use symfony with apache enable this for the public directory and set the public directory as DocumentRoot:
```
       <IfModule mod_rewrite.c>
            Options -MultiViews
            RewriteEngine On
            RewriteCond %{REQUEST_FILENAME} !-f
            RewriteRule ^(.*)$ index.php [QSA,L]
        </IfModule>

```
